  <prompt>
    Refactor @spaarke/auth to support a pluggable strategy pattern. Define the AuthStrategy interface, lift the existing MSAL configuration logic from SpaarkeAuthProvider.ts UNCHANGED (preserving INV-1..INV-7 by literal code lift), and prepare the structure for two concrete strategy implementations (BrowserMsalStrategy in task 011, OfficeNaaStrategy in task 080).

    NO behavior change in this task — just structural refactor. SpaarkeAuthProvider.ts becomes orchestrator + strategy invoker; the actual MSAL setup moves into a new BrowserMsalStrategy.ts (stub for now, full impl in 011). Drop BridgeStrategy.ts, XrmStrategy.ts, tokenBridge.ts entirely.
  </prompt>
  <role>Senior TypeScript engineer with MSAL.js + browser auth expertise. Care + caution on the MSAL config lift — INV-1..INV-7 must be preserved exactly.</role>
  <goal>
    @spaarke/auth has a new src/strategies/AuthStrategy.ts interface. SpaarkeAuthProvider.ts is refactored to use it. BrowserMsalStrategy stub exists. BridgeStrategy.ts, XrmStrategy.ts, tokenBridge.ts are deleted. types.ts updated to remove window.__SPAARKE_BFF_TOKEN__ global declaration. MSAL invariants preserved via code review (INV-1..INV-7 verified by reading the new BrowserMsalStrategy constructor against the old SpaarkeAuthProvider lines 44-83).
  </goal>
