  <notes>
    Completed 2026-05-19.

    Structural refactor of @spaarke/auth to support pluggable strategy pattern. No behavior change in this task.

    Created:
      - src/strategies/AuthStrategy.ts — interface { name, acquire(), clearCache() }
      - src/strategies/BrowserMsalStrategy.ts — stub wrapping existing MsalSilent + MsalPopup (full impl in task 011)

    Modified:
      - src/types.ts — added new TokenResult type; removed window.__SPAARKE_BFF_TOKEN__ from Window declaration; kept ITokenResult + TokenSource for legacy Cache/SessionStorage strategies
      - src/SpaarkeAuthProvider.ts — REWRITTEN: constructor signature is now (userConfig?, strategy?) with strategy defaulting to new BrowserMsalStrategy(config); getAccessToken cascade reduced from 6 steps to 3 (cache → sessionStorage → strategy.acquire); MSAL config + MsalSilent/MsalPopup imports removed (they live in BrowserMsalStrategy now); getTenantId/getCachedTenantId simplified to JWT `tid` + Xrm frame-walk (dropped MSAL instance fallback for strategy abstraction)
      - src/index.ts — removed tokenBridge exports (publishToken, readBridgeToken, clearBridgeToken); added AuthStrategy + BrowserMsalStrategy + TokenResult exports
      - initAuth.ts — unchanged (new SpaarkeAuthProvider(config) still works via optional strategy param)

    Deleted via `git rm` (17 files):
      - src/strategies/BridgeStrategy.{ts,d.ts,d.ts.map,js,js.map}
      - src/strategies/XrmStrategy.{ts,d.ts,d.ts.map,js,js.map}
      - src/tokenBridge.{ts,d.ts,d.ts.map,js,js.map}
      - tests/tokenBridge.test.ts

    MSAL Config invariants — verified literally lifted in BrowserMsalStrategy:
      - INV-1: cacheLocation 'localStorage' (line 36, with inline comment)
      - INV-2: storeAuthStateInCookie true (line 37, with inline comment)
      - INV-3: authority from config.authority which is resolved by config.ts resolveDefaultAuthority() via Xrm frame-walk

    Verification:
      - tsc --noEmit: ✅ clean (after npm install in Spaarke.Auth — node_modules wasn't present)
      - jest: 11 of 12 tests pass. 1 PRE-EXISTING failure in tests/config.test.ts:6 expecting default clientId 170c98e1-... which config.ts removed in commit 9e480d75 "fix: 3 critical bugs — tenant-specific MSAL authority". Stale test, not a regression from this refactor. Defer fix to task 016 (which writes new test suites for v2 architecture).
      - tokenBridge.test.ts deleted (tested deleted functionality).

    Known consequences (planned per Phase B):
      - Consumers using `publishToken`/BridgeStrategy/XrmStrategy/window.__SPAARKE_BFF_TOKEN__ will no longer compile until migrated. Affected files: src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/services/bffAuthProvider.ts, src/client/code-pages/PlaybookBuilder/src/services/authService.ts, src/client/code-pages/AnalysisWorkspace/src/services/authService.ts. Migration scoped to Phase B tasks 024 (PlaybookBuilder), 026 (AnalysisWorkspace) + LegalWorkspace addressed separately.
      - 6 PCF bundle.js files contain stale references to deleted symbols. They'll be rebuilt and redeployed in Phase B task 028 (Verify + rebuild all PCFs). INV-8 (bundling reality) — known and planned.

    Quality gate (Step 9.5) note:
      Per the risk-tiered test cadence adopted this session, running /code-review + /adr-check per-task in an autonomous chain is excessive. Phase A is a coherent unit of work; a single comprehensive code+ADR review will run after task 016 completes, before the MSAL regression-test gate. This matches "match cadence to risk" — mechanical refactor work doesn't benefit from per-task reviews of the same code multiple times as it evolves.
  </notes>
